headline: 3 Industrials Stocks with Mounting Challenges
summary: Industrials businesses quietly power the physical things we depend on, from cars and homes to e-commerce infrastructure. Still, their generally high capital requirements expose them to the ups and downs of economic cycles, and the market seems to be baking in a prolonged downturn as the industry has shed 10.4% over the past six months. This drop was worse than the S&P 500’s 1.9% decline.
